{"word":"πότιμος","slug":"πότιμος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πότιμος</b></el> <el>(πότιμος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πότος'><el>πότος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>of water, <i>drinkable, fresh</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>fresh, sweet, pleasant</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—of persons, <i>mild, gentle</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}